dc_title_s: Important Farmland, San Luis Obispo County, California, 1996
dc_description_s: This polygon shapefile represents areas of important farmland in San Luis Obispo County, California for 1996. Established in 1982, Government Code Section 65570 mandates FMMP to biennially report on the conversion of farmland and grazing land, and to provide maps and data to local government and the public.The Farmland Mapping and Monitoring Program (FMMP) provides data to decision makers for use in planning for the present and future use of California's agricultural land resources. The data is a current inventory of agricultural resources. This data is for general planning purposes and has a minimum mapping unit of ten acres.
